title: Mannahatta: A Natural History of New York City - Eric Sanderson
short_description: The story of Manhattan is the story of America itself. From its humble beginnings as a Lenape settlement to its current status as a global metropolis, Manhattan has been a place of innovation, creativity, and opportunity. In this book, Eric W. Sanderson tells the story of Manhattan through the lens of its cultural history. He explores the citys diverse neighborhoods, its iconic landmarks, and its rich history of art, music, and literature. Along the way, he introduces us to the people who have shaped Manhattans culture, from the Native Americans who first inhabited the island to the immigrants who have flocked to its shores from all over the world. Manhattan is a place of constant change, but its cultural history is a reminder of the enduring values that have made it a beacon of hope for people from all walks of life.
column11: National Geographic: A Cultural History of New York City: Manhattan
